      "content": "\"But consider this: they possess neither the intellectual capacity nor the moral maturity to chart their own course through such darkness. While they peer blindly into the void of superstition, our government allows them no doubt that we are born to be their shepherds, guiding them from their own incompetence. It is thus not an imposition, but a divine and natural right upon us to assemble their scattered peoples under our direction and lift them from their primitive stagnation. Let however reluctant they are, we must step forward as their only masters, for only through our superior light can they ever hope to emerge from the shadows of their own ignorance.\"",
